2. modules/voice_detector.py — get_likely_voices_for_book
What changed: Replaced 3-method pipeline (JSON + run.log + filename patterns) with 3-source pipeline (JSON → TTS copy → Voice_Samples). Removed get_voice_from_log call path. Added get_audio_prompt_path_from_json and get_voices_from_tts_dir.
Old pipeline:
Method 1: JSON voice_used → resolve via find_voice_file_by_name() or find_voice_in_tts_dir()
Method 2: run.log "Voice:" line → resolve same way
Method 3: Book root *.wav/*.m4b [VoiceName] → resolve same way
New pipeline:
# JSON voice_used → prefers TTS copy first, seeds from audio_prompt_path if missing, falls back to Voice_Samples
if chunks_json_path:
    voice_from_json = get_voice_from_json(chunks_json_path)
    if voice_from_json:
        voice_path = find_voice_in_tts_dir(voice_from_json, book_name)
        if not voice_path:
            stored_prompt_path = get_audio_prompt_path_from_json(chunks_json_path)
            source_path = stored_prompt_path if stored_prompt_path and stored_prompt_path.exists() \
                         else find_voice_file_by_name(voice_from_json)
            if source_path:
                tts_dir = Path(AUDIOBOOK_ROOT) / book_name / "TTS"
                voice_path = Path(ensure_voice_sample_compatibility(source_path, tts_dir))
        if voice_path:
            likely_voices.append((voice_from_json, voice_path, "json_metadata"))

# TTS scan — every _ttsready.wav in book TTS folder
for voice_name, voice_path in get_voices_from_tts_dir(book_name):
    if not any(v[0].casefold() == voice_name.casefold() for v in likely_voices):
        likely_voices.append((voice_name, voice_path, "tts_directory"))

# Voice_Samples scan — every audio file
for voice_path in list_voice_samples():
    voice_name = voice_path.stem.removesuffix("_ttsready")
    if not any(v[0].casefold() == voice_name.casefold() for v in likely_voices):
        likely_voices.append((voice_name, voice_path, "voice_samples"))
New helper functions:
def get_audio_prompt_path_from_json(json_path):
    """Return saved original prompt path from JSON metadata when it still exists."""
    with open(json_path, 'r') as f:
        data = json.load(f)
    if isinstance(data, dict):
        audio_prompt_path = data.get('audio_prompt_path')
    elif isinstance(data, list) and data and isinstance(data[0], dict):
        audio_prompt_path = data[0].get('audio_prompt_path')
    else:
        audio_prompt_path = None
    return Path(audio_prompt_path) if audio_prompt_path else None

def get_voices_from_tts_dir(book_name):
    """Return (voice_name, path) for every WAV in Audiobook/<book>/TTS/."""
    tts_dir = Path(AUDIOBOOK_ROOT) / book_name / "TTS"
    if not tts_dir.exists():
        return []
    return [
        (f.stem.removesuffix("_ttsready"), f)
        for f in sorted(tts_dir.glob("*.wav"), key=lambda p: p.stem.casefold())
    ]
